    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.9"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        955 <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> Sepulveda
                        Los Angeles 49, Calif.
                        July 9, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Good News! I signed a contract yesterday to teach full time at <hi rend="caps">UCLA</hi>. I will continue to work on my Ph. D. which I hope to complete in another five years or so. I also had a chance for a job at the Pt. Mugu Naval Base forty miles north of Los Angeles as a Motion Picture Producer-Director at a slightly higher salery<sic>salary</sic> but after a little soul-searching I decided that teaching was my fi<del>le</del><add>el</add>d. I enjoy teaching and feel that I will make a good teacher.</p>
                
                <p>Anyway, I will get my first pay check in August since my contract starts July 1st, and will be able to start paying back the rest of the loan. I believe I still owe you $160.00. I'm sorry to have taken so long to pay back on it but I have been a little strapped for funds. My main income was from my family and I didn't feel it was proper to take their money to pay back my debts, since I would only have to ask them for more money.</p>
                
                <p>I am enclosing a copy of the mailer that I had printed. I have not sent it out yet because I still have to have some cards printed to go along with it and the total cost for postage, envelopes, cards and printing will be close to $90.00. Needless to say, I have not had the money to finish the mailer but when I start getting ste<del>dy</del><add>ad</add>y pay checks I will be able to put some mo<del>e</del><add>r</add>e money in on the records. I should be able to send out the m<del>il</del><add>ai</add>ler sometime in August or September.</p>
                
                <p>So far we have sold 29 records, 19 at the sale price of $3.35 and 10 at the wholesale price of $2.47. I have recieved several letters saying how much the buyers enjoyed the record. One quote from a letter: "Dr. Neihardt's recording exceeds even my expectations." This is typical of the comments so far.</p>
                
                <p>How are you? I have been thinking of you quite often. I hope to see you sometime this summer. I will probably be home sometime in August and will come to Columbia when I get home. We can start working on the tape for the next record then. It would be nice if we could get the master tapes done for the whole "Cycle" this summer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sandy</signed>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
        </body>
        
